            "text": " is a historic name in the world of motorsport, with the British marque founded by Brian Lister in 1954 pioneering many lightweight an aerodynamic designs. The Jaguar D-Type-powered ‘Knobbly’ is arguably its most famous racer, but it was the Lister Costin that developed its design further. This Costin found in our ",
